{"lemma":"مَسِيح","slug":"مَسِيح","root":"م.س.ح","root_slug":"م-س-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/م-س-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَسِيح","root":"مسح","pos":"N","occurrence_count":11},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n38564","n38568","n21398"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AD"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"anointed"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"messiah, Messiah","examples":[{"text":"الْمَسِيح","english":"the Messiah, Christ"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Related to مَسَحَ (masaḥa, “to anoint”). Cognate to Aramaic ܡܫܺܝܚܳܐ (m'šīḥāʿ) and Hebrew מָשִׁיחַ (mashíakh), whence the Ancient Greek borrowing Μεσσίας (Messías) and the Greek calque Χριστός (Christós), thus the English terms \"Messiah\" and \"Christ\"."},"ipa":["/ma.siːħ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38564","headword_ar":"مَسِيحٌ","root":"msH","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anointed: wiped over with some such thing as oil."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A king."},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-'Eynee.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmasiyHu","text_ar":"المَسِيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Messiah, the Christ, the Anointed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Jesus,"},{"kind":"text","text":"on whom be peace ! (S, Msb, K,) [correctly] an arabicized word, [from the Hebrew,] originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$iyHaA","text_ar":"مَشِيحَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$","text_ar":"ش"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, Msb:) but the learned differ as to this word, whether it be Arabic or arabicized: F relates, in the K, his having mentioned, in his Expos. of the Meshárik el-Anwár, fifty opinions respecting the derivation of it; and in another work he has made the number fifty-six. (TA.) ―         -b4-  Also, (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmasiyHu Alka*~aAbu","text_ar":"المَسِيحُ الكَذَّابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almis~iyHu","text_ar":"المِسِّيحُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Messiah,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Christ, surnamed the Great Liar; the False Christ; Antichrist;"},{"kind":"text","text":"also called]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"EdDejjál,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aj~aAlu","text_ar":"الدَّجَّالُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) it is not allowable, however, to apply to him the appellation"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmasiyHu","text_ar":"المَسِيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"without restriction; wherefore one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmasiyHu","text_ar":"المَسِيحُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aj~aAlu","text_ar":"الدَّجَّالُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alka*~aAbu","text_ar":"الكَذَّابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (TA;) [unless in a case like the following, in which] a poet says"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_i*aA AlmasiyHu yaqotulu AlmasiyHa"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When the true Messiah shall slay the"},{"kind":"text","text":"false"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Messiah"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Msb.) [Many opinions respecting the derivation of the appellation thus applied are also mentioned by various authors.] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyHN","text_ar":"مَسِيحٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sweat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K:) so called because it is wiped off ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yumosaHu","text_ar":"يُمْسَحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":") when it pours forth. (T.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyHN","text_ar":"مَسِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  A dirhem [or silver coin]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the impression is obliterated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTolasu","text_ar":"اَطْلَسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no impression."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyHN","text_ar":"مَسِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyHapN","text_ar":"مَسِيحَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of silver."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, K.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyHN","text_ar":"مَسِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mamosuwHu Alwajohi","text_ar":"مَمْسُوحُ الوَجْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) i.e., A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having one side of his face plain, without eye"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eyebrow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"said to apply in this sense to EdDejjál, among others. (IF, L.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One-eyed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amosaHu","text_ar":"اَمْسَحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyHN","text_ar":"مَسِيحٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rough napkin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kerchief, with which one wipes himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K:) so called because the face is wiped with it, or because it retains the dirt. (TA.) [A dusting-cloth, or dish-clout, or the like, is now called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mimosaHapN","text_ar":"مِمْسَحَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyHN","text_ar":"مَسِيحٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beautiful in the face."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyHN","text_ar":"مَسِيحٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who journeys"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goes about much for the sake of devotion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a devotee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mis~iyHN","text_ar":"مِسِّيحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amosaHu","text_ar":"اَمْسَحُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) the fem. of which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masoHaA='u","text_ar":"مَسْحَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~aAHN","text_ar":"مَسَّاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyHN","text_ar":"مَسِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Multum coiens;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAsiHN","text_ar":"مَاسِحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyHN","text_ar":"مَسِيحٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Erring greatly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyHN","text_ar":"مَسِيحٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A great liar; one who lies much;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAsiHN","text_ar":"مَاسِحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mimosaHN","text_ar":"مِمْسَحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"timosaHN","text_ar":"تِمْسَحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amosaHu","text_ar":"اَمْسَحُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) the fem. of which last is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masoHaA='u","text_ar":"مَسْحَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAsiHN","text_ar":"مَاسِحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyHN","text_ar":"مَسِيحٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Very veracious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sid~iyqN","text_ar":"صِدِّيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, L, TA: in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadiyqN","text_ar":"صَدِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) a meaning unknown to many of the lexicologists, and probably obsolete in their time. (L.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyHN","text_ar":"مَسِيحٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Created blessed, and goodly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"created"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mamosuwHN","text_ar":"مَمْسُوحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with blessing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prosperity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) ―         -b2-  and, contr.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"created accursed, and foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ugly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"created with unfortunateness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","T","TA","L","Lh"]},{"entry_id":"n38568","headword_ar":"مِسِّيحٌ","root":"msH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almis~iyHu","text_ar":"المِسِّيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiyHN","text_ar":"مَسِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n21398","headword_ar":"مُسَيَّحٌ","root":"syH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Striped;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied in this sense to a [garment of the kind called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burod","text_ar":"بُرْد"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) and also, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", to a [garment such as is called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabaA='ap","text_ar":"عَبَا=ءَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or applied to [the garments called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabaA='","text_ar":"عَبَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having alternate stripes of white and black, the latter not intensely black:"},{"kind":"text","text":"every"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EbA'p","text_ar":"عباءة"},{"kind":"text","text":"also is termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayoHN","text_ar":"سَيْحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musay~aHapN","text_ar":"مُسَيَّحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but that which has not stripes is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='","text_ar":"كِسَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", not an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EbA'p","text_ar":"عباءة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (ISh, TA.) So too applied to locusts ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaraAd","text_ar":"جَرَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":"); (K;) and with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a single locust [i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaraAdap","text_ar":"جَرَادَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) or, applied to locusts, it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"marked with black and yellow and white stripes"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"streaks."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, TA.) It is also applied as an epithet to the [bird called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayoquTaAn","text_ar":"حَيْقُطَان"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild ass:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because of his streak that makes a division between the belly and the side. (K, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musay~aHu AlEajiyzapi","text_ar":"مُسَيَّحُ العَجِيزَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He that has the rump streaked"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is an epithet applied to the [wild] ass because of the whiteness on his rump. (A, TA.) ―         -b3-  (tropical:)  A road"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the tracks"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arak","text_ar":"شَرَك"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uruk","text_ar":"شُرُك"},{"kind":"text","text":"in different copies of the K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are rendered apparent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabaA='","text_ar":"عَبَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus termed. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}